{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-07",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_07_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "07 - A Mad Tea-party",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.757,
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 242.56,
  "page_end_sec": 485.06,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 242.56,
      "end": 243.08,
      "text": "\"Of course not,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 243.24,
      "end": 244.46,
      "text": "Alice replied very readily:"
    },
    {
      "start": 245.32,
      "end": 246.9,
      "text": "\"but that's because it stays the same"
    },
    {
      "start": 246.9,
      "end": 248.42,
      "text": "year for such a long time together.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 250.08,
      "end": 251.52,
      "text": "\"Which is just the case with _mine_,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 251.84,
      "end": 252.52,
      "text": "said the Hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.76,
      "end": 255.3,
      "text": "Alice felt dreadfully puzzled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 255.66,
      "end": 258.4,
      "text": "The Hatter's remark seemed to have no meaning in it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 258.44,
      "end": 259.74,
      "text": "and yet it was certainly English."
    },
    {
      "start": 261.21,
      "end": 262.66,
      "text": "\"I don't quite understand,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 263.02,
      "end": 264.66,
      "text": "she said, as politely as she could."
    },
    {
      "start": 266.24,
      "end": 267.66,
      "text": "\"The Dormouse is asleep again,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 267.86,
      "end": 268.54,
      "text": "said the Hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 268.64,
      "end": 270.88,
      "text": "and he poured a little hot tea upon its nose."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.86,
      "end": 274.18,
      "text": "The Dormouse shook its head impatiently,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 274.2,
      "end": 276.12,
      "text": "and said, without opening its eyes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.52,
      "end": 276.92,
      "text": "\"Of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 277.1,
      "end": 277.7,
      "text": "of course;"
    },
    {
      "start": 277.84,
      "end": 280.26,
      "text": "just what I was going to remark myself.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 281.76,
      "end": 282.9,
      "text": "\"Have you guessed the riddle yet?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 283.02,
      "end": 283.74,
      "text": "the Hatter said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 283.8,
      "end": 284.82,
      "text": "turning to Alice again."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.38,
      "end": 285.48,
      "text": "\"No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.82,
      "end": 286.5,
      "text": "I give it up,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 286.5,
      "end": 287.06,
      "text": "Alice replied:"
    },
    {
      "start": 287.3,
      "end": 287.94,
      "text": "\"what's the answer?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 288.74,
      "end": 290.4,
      "text": "\"I haven't the slightest idea,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 290.62,
      "end": 291.22,
      "text": "said the Hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.34,
      "end": 292.7,
      "text": "\"Nor I,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 292.98,
      "end": 293.78,
      "text": "said the March Hare."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.0,
      "end": 297.0,
      "text": "Alice sighed wearily.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 297.66,
      "end": 300.32,
      "text": "\"I think you might do something better with the time,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 300.54,
      "end": 300.94,
      "text": "she said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.06,
      "end": 303.24,
      "text": "\"than wasting it asking riddles with no answers.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 305.02,
      "end": 306.96,
      "text": "\"If you knew Time as well as I do,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 307.12,
      "end": 307.72,
      "text": "said the Hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 308.22,
      "end": 310.22,
      "text": "\"you wouldn't talk about wasting _it_."
    },
    {
      "start": 310.34,
      "end": 311.24,
      "text": "It's _him_.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 313.06,
      "end": 314.08,
      "text": "\"I don't know what you mean,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 314.26,
      "end": 314.68,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.14,
      "end": 317.8,
      "text": "\"Of course you don't!\" the Hatter said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 317.9,
      "end": 319.18,
      "text": "tossing his head contemptuously."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.98,
      "end": 322.1,
      "text": "\"I daresay you never spoke to Time!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 323.296,
      "end": 325.28,
      "text": "\"Perhaps not,\" Alice cautiously replied:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 326.04,
      "end": 328.52,
      "text": "\"but I know I have to beat time when I learn music.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 328.96,
      "end": 329.74,
      "text": "\"Ah!"
    },
    {
      "start": 329.96,
      "end": 331.88,
      "text": "that accounts for it,\" said the Hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.24,
      "end": 333.6,
      "text": "\"He won't stand beating."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.04,
      "end": 334.14,
      "text": "Now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 334.42,
      "end": 336.74,
      "text": "if you only kept on good terms with him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.8,
      "end": 339.2,
      "text": "he'd do almost anything you liked with the clock."
    },
    {
      "start": 339.96,
      "end": 340.38,
      "text": "For instance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 340.62,
      "end": 342.6,
      "text": "suppose it were nine o'clock in the morning,"
    },
    {
      "start": 342.8,
      "end": 344.12,
      "text": "just time to begin lessons:"
    },
    {
      "start": 344.48,
      "end": 346.84,
      "text": "you'd only have to whisper a hint to Time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.12,
      "end": 348.72,
      "text": "and round goes the clock in a twinkling!"
    },
    {
      "start": 349.4,
      "end": 350.0,
      "text": "Half-past one,"
    },
    {
      "start": 350.16,
      "end": 351.04,
      "text": "time for dinner!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 352.85,
      "end": 354.46,
      "text": "(\"I only wish it was,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 354.92,
      "end": 357.06,
      "text": "the March Hare said to itself in a whisper.)"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.22,
      "end": 359.24,
      "text": "\"That would be grand, certainly,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 359.54,
      "end": 360.64,
      "text": "said Alice thoughtfully:"
    },
    {
      "start": 361.42,
      "end": 363.26,
      "text": "\"but then--I shouldn't be hungry for it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.32,
      "end": 363.58,
      "text": "you know.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 365.216,
      "end": 365.94,
      "text": "\"Not at first,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 365.96,
      "end": 366.22,
      "text": "perhaps,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 366.54,
      "end": 367.24,
      "text": "said the Hatter:"
    },
    {
      "start": 367.62,
      "end": 370.62,
      "text": "\"but you could keep it to half-past one as long as you liked.\""

    },
    {
      "start": 371.96,
      "end": 373.22,
      "text": "\"Is that the way _you_ manage?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 373.48,
      "end": 374.2,
      "text": "Alice asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 374.65,
      "end": 376.8,
      "text": "The Hatter shook his head mournfully."
    },
    {
      "start": 377.92,
      "end": 382.34,
      "text": "\"Not I!\" he replied. \"We quarrelled last March----just before _he_ went",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 382.34,
      "end": 385.3,
      "text": "mad, you know----\" (pointing with his teaspoon to the March Hare),"
    },
    {
      "start": 386.14,
      "end": 388.04,
      "text": "\"it was at the great concert given by",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 388.04,
      "end": 390.3,
      "text": "the Queen of Hearts, and I had to sing"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.424,
      "end": 392.96,
      "text": "'Twinkle, twinkle, little bat!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 393.7,
      "end": 397.26,
      "text": "How I wonder what you're at!' You know that song, perhaps?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 398.68,
      "end": 400.26,
      "text": "\"I've heard something like it,\" said Alice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 401.56,
      "end": 404.56,
      "text": "\"It goes on, you know,\" the Hatter continued, \"in this way:--",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 405.52,
      "end": 410.76,
      "text": "'Up above the world you fly,\nLike a tea-tray in the sky.\n            Twinkle, twinkle----'\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 413.08,
      "end": 415.78,
      "text": "Here the Dormouse shook itself, and began singing",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 415.78,
      "end": 419.54,
      "text": "in its sleep \"_Twinkle, twinkle, twinkle, twinkle_----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 420.74,
      "end": 423.54,
      "text": "and went on so long that they had to pinch it to make it stop.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 424.4,
      "end": 425.2,
      "text": "\"Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 425.34,
      "end": 427.24,
      "text": "I'd hardly finished the first verse,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 427.44,
      "end": 428.08,
      "text": "said the Hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 428.18,
      "end": 430.58,
      "text": "\"when the Queen jumped up and bawled out"
    },
    {
      "start": 430.8,
      "end": 432.02,
      "text": "'He's murdering the time!"
    },
    {
      "start": 432.32,
      "end": 433.36,
      "text": "Off with his head!'\""
    },
    {
      "start": 435.32,
      "end": 436.34,
      "text": "\"How dreadfully savage!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 436.52,
      "end": 437.3,
      "text": "exclaimed Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 438.72,
      "end": 439.56,
      "text": "\"And ever since that,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 439.74,
      "end": 441.52,
      "text": "the Hatter went on in a mournful tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.96,
      "end": 443.82,
      "text": "\"he won't do a thing I ask!"
    },
    {
      "start": 444.02,
      "end": 445.96,
      "text": "It's always six o'clock now.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 447.0,
      "end": 449.52,
      "text": "A bright idea came into Alice's head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 450.6,
      "end": 453.4,
      "text": "\"Is that the reason so many tea-things are put out here?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 453.54,
      "end": 454.06,
      "text": "she asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 455.09,
      "end": 455.64,
      "text": "\"Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 455.76,
      "end": 456.36,
      "text": "that's it,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 456.42,
      "end": 457.8,
      "text": "said the Hatter with a sigh:"
    },
    {
      "start": 458.496,
      "end": 459.92,
      "text": "\"it's always tea-time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 460.02,
      "end": 462.58,
      "text": "and we've no time to wash the things between whiles.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 463.44,
      "end": 464.44,
      "text": "\"Then you keep moving round,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 464.64,
      "end": 465.04,
      "text": "I suppose?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 465.36,
      "end": 465.9,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 466.688,
      "end": 467.52,
      "text": "\"Exactly so,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 467.72,
      "end": 468.46,
      "text": "said the Hatter:"
    },
    {
      "start": 468.54,
      "end": 470.02,
      "text": "\"as the things get used up.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 471.34,
      "end": 473.22,
      "text": "\"But what happens when you come to the beginning again?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 473.42,
      "end": 474.52,
      "text": "Alice ventured to ask."
    },
    {
      "start": 475.456,
      "end": 477.78,
      "text": "\"Suppose we change the subject,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 478.22,
      "end": 479.34,
      "text": "the March Hare interrupted,"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.54,
      "end": 479.9,
      "text": "yawning."
    },
    {
      "start": 480.94,
      "end": 482.32,
      "text": "\"I'm getting tired of this.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 482.46,
      "end": 485.06,
      "text": "I vote the young lady tells us a story.\""
    }
  ]
}
